==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tupaiid
<hw>Tu*pai"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of East Indian and Asiatic insectivores
of the family <fam>Tupaiidae</fam>, somewhat resembling squirrels in
size and arboreal habits. The nose is long and pointed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tupelo</ent>⟦br⟧
